org.lenskit.data.events

Class LikeBatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lenskit.data.events.LikeBatch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Event

    @BuiltBy(value=LikeBatchBuilder.class)
public class LikeBatch
extends Object
implements Event

    Generic interface representing a batch of unary interactions. Events of this type will generally not have timestamps. An example of a use of this event type is to represent play counts in a summarized data set.

    Like batches can be constructed with LikeBatchBuilder or create(long, long, int).

    Since:
    2.2
